Class ICalReader

java.lang.Object
  biweekly.io.text.ICalReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
IParser, Closeable
public class ICalReader
extends Object
implements IParser

Parses ICalendar objects from an iCalendar data stream. 

 Reader reader = ...
 ICalReader icalReader = new ICalReader(reader);
 ICalendar ical;
 while ((ical = icalReader.readNext()) != null){
   ...
 }
 icalReader.close();

Method Detail

isCaretDecodingEnabled

public boolean isCaretDecodingEnabled()
Gets whether the reader will decode parameter values that use circumflex accent encoding. This escaping mechanism allows newlines and double quotes to be included in parameter values. It is enabled by default.

Returns:
true if circumflex accent decoding is enabled, false if not
See Also:
ICalRawReader.isCaretDecodingEnabled()

setCaretDecodingEnabled

public void setCaretDecodingEnabled(boolean enable)
Sets whether the reader will decode parameter values that use circumflex accent encoding. This escaping mechanism allows newlines and double quotes to be included in parameter values. It is enabled by default.

Parameters:
enable - true to use circumflex accent decoding, false not to

getWarnings

public List<String> getWarnings()
Description copied from interface: IParser
Gets the warnings from the last iCalendar object that was unmarshalled. This list is reset every time a new iCalendar object is read.
